				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well, I can provide one reason: All this is causing a lot of people who don't know crap about playing their class to reach high levels, who then proceed to make grouping experiences lame for many people by repeatedly getting their groups killed, etc. It used to be that, at least usually, finding people with good gear for their level indicated an experienced player, but it really doesn't anymore. (Although of course plat buying/selling has been around for many years.)
<br />

<br />
That's SoE's fault to some degree, though. With how insanely cheap mid-level items are at this point, lower lvl high EXP zones like PC and LDoNs are a total joke. I remember a lvl 35ish LDoN I took part in where the entire group was just running around the zone slaughtering everything in moments. The cleric didn't even have to med, he just meleed with his Delightful Orb. That kind of trivalization often means that people who have no idea how to play their class effectively still easily level up to their 50s. But like I said, that has more to do with SoE constantly introducing better and better and easier to get items into the game than it does with plat selling.
<br />

<br />
I guess in the end, I don't really see how buying plat online is so bad for EQ either. As I've said before, I think the effect plat buying has on the economy in EQ is not even all negative. It's still lame, though. It's using RL assets to trivialize game content and set heirarchies in a game where the 'community' is very important to most people.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=869368" target="_blank" class="postlink">Succor</a>
