				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I don't think buying PP with real money is cheatig, but I can understand why it bothers so many people.
<br />

<br />
When we play EQ, we have this idea that we are playing in a self-contained universe, with it's own laws and *internal* consistency. Everything that happens, happens *within* the game, and most people enjoy that facet of the game.
<br />

<br />
Now, when it's possible to have real life influence in-game events, it destroys the sense of playing in a self-contained world. EQ has been contaminated by events from RL.
<br />

<br />
This bothers some people. It intereferes with the fun, joy, escapism, or whatever you'd like to call it, of EQ. It is a reminder of the RL world that, let's face it, if we loved so much we wouldn't be playing EQ so often.
<br />

<br />
So, people complain about 'cheating.' Well, maybe it's cheating, maybe it's not, but it is an evolution or perversion of the game that can destroy or limit the fun that other *non-playerauction*  plays have.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
