			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">EverQuest was developed by Verant, which is now owned by Sony. To play the game, you agree to the contents of the EULA, by clicking the OK button. It's a game. Games have rules. The EULA is part of those rules.
<br />

<br />
Direct quote from the EULA, section 9: "You may not sell or auction any EverQuest characters, items, coin or copyrighted material"
<br />

<br />
Meriam-Webster online, direct quote from the word "cheating", section 1b: "to violate rules dishonestly"
<br />

<br />
It doesn't get any plainer than that. 
<br />

<br />
Selling items from accounts is cheating and could very well be argued illegal, by software piracy laws and copyright laws, since you are selling Sonys intellectual property. When you buy the software for EQ, all you are doing is licensing it. You do not own anything, period, end of story.
<br />

<br />
Of course, people that feel that it's not cheating are like those people that download MP3's for free and don't think it's illegal. People like that just dont get it and only follow the rules/laws when its convenient for them. Of course, theyll argue their point to no end and try to justify it any way they can (at least to themselves, which is all that matters to them), probably flaming me for several pages, but, people like that are perpetually clueless.
<br />

<br />
Morally, it cheapens the game and lessens the play quality of the people playing within the rules, especially when it affects prices in game and when we have to deal with incompetent toons that just bought their uber-character from an auction site and have no idea on how to play that class/level.
<br />

<br />
The only harm I wish upon Yantis/IGE and anyone else involved in this, is a complete wipe of all accounts that they own/control, or have participated with, along with a lifetime ban from EQ and any other Sony online games. Also, it would be nice to know if they are claiming this income with the IRS. A nice audit, maybe tipped off by Sony (right after confiscation and deletion of all said accounts), would put a smile on my face.     <img src="images/smiles/icon_twisted.gif" alt="Twisted Evil" border="0" /></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
