				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Well you have to think that things are already in a vicious cycle. People have set these INSANE prices on things in the bazaar so people find that they need more money.  They buy online (some of them), while others spend hours upon hours of farming to get the money, only to find that someone bought what you wanted and the next person is selling it for an even more jacked up price then the last.
<br />

<br />
Personally I've thought about buying plat online for these paticular reason.  Have I done it?  No.  Tho I can understand why some would go that route.  
<br />

<br />
Example.  I play on the Povar server.  When I was a younger Mage, I saw Rathe's Son selling 30k in the Bazaar.  I thought to myself, "Jeebus Cripes, what's wrong with these people."  Just the other day I saw it selling for 45k.  15k more so then before.  Thru a EP turn in I got Xegony's Phantasmal Guard twice, so I went to the bazaar, loaded up trader, and looked around to see other peoples prices.  Now me, I always undercut people if I find thier prices rediculos.  Guess what... I saw the spell being sold for 20k  I promptly sold mine for 1k.  
<br />

<br />
If people weren't so bloody greedy, then we wouldn't have to worry about things like this.  Mages get screwed with their spell research and droppage enough to not need yahoo's doing things like this.  IMHO<br />_________________<br />"Here's your mana rod. How much do you think I like you? I dare you. Experience a mystical transvergence." - Coconice
