				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">We're talking about Yantis/IGE and SOE here, and whether its cheating, 
<br />

<br />
not whether or not you suck as a mage, maybe you dont, maybe you do. i really dont care, 
<br />

<br />
BUT when people never learn how to earn/do things without an outside help, they dont/cant/never will discipline themselves enough to learn how to do them without the help...its like being addicted to drugs, once in, it takes an extreme amount of self-discipline to get off them.
<br />

<br />
but if you are born on drugs, (ie, your mother was taking drugs while she was pregnant.) there are lots more problems. 
<br />

<br />
buying plat is cheating, period. 
<br />

<br />
if you cheat to get where you are, you dont learn. 
<br />

<br />
if you didnt cheat to get where you are, you did learn.
<br />

<br />
if you didnt cheat to get where you are, but now do cheat to get more. you're the guy who started doing drugs, but wasnt born on them, and i still dont want to play with you.
<br />

<br />
sure you may be a good mage, but that doesnt change the fact that you cheat!
<br />
and if you cheat in one area of the game, how could i possibly trust you to be legit in another area? 
<br />

<br />
if you cheat, it shows you have a weakness with honesty, and i dont want to deal with dishonest people. 
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
true the game is full of greedy bastards, but thats no excuse to cheat to pay for their over priced stuff. 
<br />

<br />
i have yet to see a droppable item ingame that i would sell for more than 50k. 
<br />
in fact i sold my monks SoD for 70k, because thats what its worth. 
<br />

<br />
and yet i still see people sitting in the baz for HOURS trying to pawn them off for 500k+ using the excuse that they no longer drop for the outrageous price. 
